Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Hasan Mahmud strikes! The bowling change works for Bangladesh and they finally get the crucial breakthrough that they were craving all morning. This one is on a good length and in that channel outside off, holds its line again. Wiaan Mulder stays back and tries to push at it with no footwork at all. He gets another outside edge and this time it carries to the wide first slip where Shadman Islam makes no mistake. Mulder looks up in the skies in disappointment but he has played his part with a fine 54 off 112! Bangladesh break the 119-run stand and South Africa are now 227/7!
Default_Commentary: 64.5: Hasan Mahmud to Wiaan Mulder, OUT! c Shadman Islam b Hasan Mahmud.
Howout: c Shadman Islam b Hasan Mahmud

Commentary: OUT! BOWLED'EM! Hasan Mahmud with the double whammy here! A hint of reverse swing and Keshav Maharaj walks back for a golden duck. This is bowled from wide of the crease and fuller, off, shaping in and keeps a bit low too. Keshav Maharaj stays back in his crease and crouches low to play at it but is late into his shot. The ball sneaks through the gap between bat and pad and uproots the off stump. South Africa all of a sudden are eight down now with a 121-run lead! Also, Hasan Mahmud will be on a hat-trick in his next over!
Default_Commentary: 64.6: Hasan Mahmud to Keshav Maharaj, OUT! b Hasan Mahmud.
Howout: b Hasan Mahmud

Commentary: MISSED STUMPING! A rush of blood almost costs Mahmudul Hasan Joy his wicket here. This is tossed up, full and on middle, Joy skips down the track for a wild slog across the line but misses it completely. The ball hits a rough and bounces a bit more as the keeper, Kyle Verreynne has to collect it near his chest height and by the time he breaks the stumps, Joy dives back to get his bat inside. It is sent upstairs to check to be absolutely sure. The third umpire sees a lot of replays, and there is a moment when the bat is in the air and the lights go off on the bails. But before the bat went up in the air, Mahmudul Hasan Joy managed to get some part of it behind the crease which saved him. A really close call but he survives!

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Who else? It is Kagiso Rabada once again who gets the breakthrough for South Africa. After a tight first over, he gets the reward and gets rid of the set batter here. This one is on a good length and in that channel outside off, holds its line. Mahmudul Hasan Joy stays in his crease and flashes his bat at it without any footwork. Gets a thick outside edge and David Bedingham at first slip makes no mistake. Joy falls for a well-made 40 off 92, but the hosts are rocked early on Day 3 here.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! An excellent review from South Africa! Aiden Markram takes the review with only a second left in the timer, but it proves to be a great call. Keshav Maharaj tosses it up, full and on off, turns away sharply. Litton Das strides out to defend but the ball bounces a bit more than expected and goes past the shoulder of the bat and Kyle Verreynne grabs it well behind the stumps. There is a loud appeal for caught behind, but the umpire says no. Maharaj convinces his skipper to go upstairs and UltraEdge comes up with a spike. Jubilation among the Proteas and they are inching closer to the win now!

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Tony de Zorzi cannot believe he has picked out the fielder here. Taijul Islam has another one! He slows it up and bowls it wider outside off as he sees Zorzi come down the track. He still goes for the shot. It goes off the toe end as he has to drag it, and it is taken well at long on by Hasan Mahmud. Tony de Zorzi walks back for 41 off 52 and will be disappointed that he could not stay till the end here.
